{
  "doc_id": "6006",
  "text": "The importance of the significant other's support in illness recovery is well-documented [CITATION_1] . Previous findings suggested that psychosocial interventions that improve both the person with cancer and the partner's social and emotional well-being may have positive effects on QOL [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . The degree of the partner's emotional involvement and understanding of the woman's experience is directly associated with psychological adjustment [CITATION_4] . In our study women in the BCT group showed more support from their partners than women in MRM, this can be of a special concern in Egypt where human relations and familial bonds are still so strong.",
